The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 10 May is 42,066 (4,868.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 May, there were 104 new confirmed cases (12.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 28 April, there were 142 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 27% (38 fewer cases).
